Target: OntoDataDoc is an ontology designed for the represention of data documentation

Comment: A collection of related data, which may include quantitative, qualitative or descriptive values
Label: Dataset

Comment: A person, organisation, software or physical artefact
Label: Agent

Comment: The broader thematic group or domain to which a dataset belongs
Label: Data Category

Comment: The main topic or theme of the dataset
Label: Subject

Comment: The source from which the data is obtained
Label: Data Source

Comment: An article describing the dataset
Label: Publication

Comment: An entity or organisation responsible for making the dataset publicly available
Label: Publisher

Comment: The elements, characteristics and relationships that constitute the contents of the dataset
Label: Data Content

Comment: A distinctive feature of a data content element
Label: Characteristic

Comment: A characteristic of data that is descriptive, categorical, or otherwise non-numeric in nature
Label: QualitativeCharacteristic

Comment: A characteristic of data that is numerical or measurable in nature
Label: QuantitativeCharacteristic

Comment: The systematic process of verifying and validating data to ensure it meets standards of accuracy, completeness, consistency, and reliability.
Label: Quality Control

Comment: A data range defines the allowable values or scope for data points, that is, an acceptable range of variations
Label: Data Range

Comment: An independent content represents data points that stand alone and are not influenced by others
Label: Independent Content

Comment: A dependent content signifies data points that rely on or are influenced by others
Label: Dependent Content

Comment: A controlled content indicates data that is subject to specific constraints or regulations
Label: Controlled Content

Comment: The data validation encompasses processes or mechanisms used to ensure the accuracy and integrity of the dataset
Label: Data Validation

Comment: The missing data identifies instances where data points are absent or incomplete
Label: Missing Data

Comment: A versioning instance tracks different versions or iterations of the dataset
Label: Versioning

Comment: The consistency check refers to a process or procedure implemented to ensure uniformity and coherence within the dataset
Label: Consistency Check

Comment: The usability testing assesses the dataset's user-friendliness and ease of use
Label: Usability Testing

Comment: The user review captures feedback and reviews from users to increase the trust nd reliability
Label: User Review

Comment: The usage guideline instance outlines recommendations, terms and conditions, rights permission, etc. for effectively utilizing the dataset
Label: Usage Guideline

Comment: The access rights specify the permissions and restrictions based on user roles and requirements associated with accessing the dataset
Label: Rights Statement

Comment: The terms and conditions outline the legal and contractual terms such as  licensing, usage restrictions, and obligations associated with the dataset's usage
Label: Terms and Conditions

Comment: A relation between a dataset and its publication, indicating when and where the dataset was officially released or made public
Label: has Publication

Comment: A relation between a dataset and its creator, identifying the individual or entity responsible for the initial development or generation of the data
Label: has Creator

Comment: A relation that establishes a link between a dataset and its contributors, recognizing individuals or entities who have contributed to the dataset beyond its creation
Label: has Contributor

Comment: A relation that indicates a format or data structure in which the dataset is presented or stored
Label: has Data Format

Comment: Specifies the category or classification to which the dataset belongs
Label: has Data Category

Comment: Establishes the linguistic context or the language of the dataset
Label: has Language

Comment: Identifies the main topic or theme of the dataset, providing a concise description of the primary focus or purpose of the data
Label: has Subject

Comment: Specifies the source or origin from which the dataset was extracted, offering insights into the data's provenance
Label: extracted From

Comment: A relation between a dataset and its validation processes to ensure the accuracy and reliability of the data
Label: has Data Validation

Comment: Establishes a connection between a dataset and its missing data information to indicate the absence or incompleteness of data
Label: has Missing Data

Comment: Specifies the version or iteration of the dataset, offering insights into the evolution and changes made over time
Label: has Version

Comment: A relation between a dataset and its consistency checking processes used to maintain uniformity within the data
Label: has Consistency Check

Comment: A relation between a dataset and usability testing, indicating efforts to assess the dataset's user-friendliness and accessibility
Label: has Usability Testing

Comment: A relation between a dataset and user reviews, capturing feedback and insights from individuals who have interacted with the data
Label: has User Review

Comment: Specifies related datasets or data entities
Label: has Relation

Comment: A relation between a dataset and its content or variable
Label: has Content

Comment: A relation between a data content and its basic building blocks or components
Label: has Element

Comment: A relation between a data content and its distinctive qualitative or quantitative characteristic
Label: has Characteristic

Comment: A relation between a quantity and its data range
Label: has Data Range

Comment: A relation between a data content and its measurement units for quantitative data
Label: has Unit

Comment: Specifies dependency on a data content
Label: depends On

Comment: Establishes the access restrictions to indicate permissions and limitations on who can access the data
Label: has Access Rights

Comment: Establishes a relation to outline the legal and contractual obligations associated with the data
Label: has Terms and Conditions

Comment: A relation between a dataset and its quality check or control pass
Label: has Quality Control Pass

Comment: Establishes a relation between a dataset and its usage guidelines, providing recommendations and best practices for utilizing the data
Label: has Usage Guideline

Comment: A relation that specifies Digital Object Identifier (DOI) of a published entity to make it publicly available
Label: has DOI

Comment: specifies the contact information of an authority to discuss about the dataset as a usage guideline
Label: has Contact

Comment: Specifies the date of copyright information at which the dataset to indicate ownership and intellectual property rights
Label: has Copyright

Comment: Specifies the name assigned to a data content for reference and identification. For example, daily rainfall (a variable in the dataset).
Label: has Name

Comment: Associates the data content with a diagram, figure or visual representation
Label: has Illustration

Comment: Specifies a person or organisation that provides the dataset
Label: provided By

Comment: A name given to the dataset. For example, Majorca region flood risk dataset.
Label: has Title

Comment: Indicates the intended outcomes associated with the dataset. For example, a dataset aimed at improving flood prediction accuracy.
Label: has Objective

Comment: Provides a description of the dataset, summarising its content and context
Label: has Description

Comment: Specifies the intended use of the dataset. For example, a dataset developed or collected for flood risk assessment.
Label: has Purpose

Comment: Specifies the date when the dataset was created
Label: has Date Created

Comment: Specifies the size of the dataset
Label: has Content Size

Comment: Specifies the maximum value
Label: has Maximum Value

Comment: Specifies the minimum value
Label: has Minimum Value

Comment: Specifies how the dataset should be cited
Label: has URL

Comment: Specifies the contact details for individuals or entities responsible for inquiries or further information related to the dataset usage
Label: has Keyword
